{% extends "demo.html.j2" %}

{% set v = card_data.vesper %}
{% set h = card_data.hensley %}
{% set quarters = v.timeline.quarters %}

{% block head_extra %}
<link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ asset_base | default('') }}assets/pages/m6.css">
{% endblock %}

{% block demo_content %}
<section class="m6-intro">
  <p class="m6-headline">
    <strong>Form 13F is a quarterly US regulatory filing</strong> that discloses selected US long
    positions. It is delayed by up to 45 days and omits shorts, so it is a view of the reported
    long book, not the whole fund. This fully synthetic example shows
    <strong>{{ v.name }}</strong>&rsquo;s visible long book compressing
    from {{ "%.1f"|format(quarters[0].effective_names) }} effective names to
    {{ "%.1f"|format(quarters[-1].effective_names) }}. The latest leader reaches
    {{ "%.1f"|format(quarters[-1].leader_share * 100) }}%, while the latest top three have
    remained visible for all six quarters. This is an engagement prompt, not a return prediction:
    <strong>Your reported book concentrated into one name &mdash; walk us through the conviction?</strong>
  </p>
  <p class="m6-source-dates">
    Q1 as of {{ quarters[0].as_of }} &middot; known at {{ quarters[0].known_at }} &middot; 45-day lag;
    Q6 as of {{ quarters[-1].as_of }} &middot; known at {{ quarters[-1].known_at }} &middot; 45-day lag
  </p>
</section>

<aside class="m6-exhibit" aria-label="What this exhibit shows">
  <h2>What this exhibit shows</h2>
  <div class="m6-exhibit__block">
    <h3>What you are looking at</h3>
    <p>A six-quarter, fully synthetic 13F crop from a simulated signed book. Shorts and
      ineligible names disappear before the surviving public longs are renormalized. The table
      therefore describes the visible crop, not the manager&rsquo;s full portfolio.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="m6-exhibit__block">
    <h3>How to read it</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>The trajectory</strong> puts all six quarters on one 0&ndash;100% scale. The bar is
        the top-five share and the dot is the largest reported position.</li>
      <li><strong>Cell shares</strong> in the later table are reported long-book weights.</li>
      <li><strong>Quarters held</strong> counts the latest unbroken reported run.</li>
      <li><strong>Effective names</strong> is inverse Herfindahl: lower means more concentrated.</li>
      <li><strong>The coverage check</strong> suppresses book-level concentration and overlap when the
        public crop covers less than 60% of true gross long weight.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>The full derivation and limits are in the
      <a href="{{ asset_base | default('') }}specs/{{ card.id }}.html">technical method</a>.</p>
  </div>
</aside>

<section class="m6-trajectory" aria-labelledby="m6-trajectory-title">
  <div class="m6-trajectory__heading">
    <div>
      <p class="m6-trajectory__eyebrow">Main visual</p>
      <h2 id="m6-trajectory-title">Six-quarter concentration trajectory</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="m6-trajectory__legend" aria-label="Trajectory legend">
      <span><i class="m6-trajectory__legend-bar"></i>Top five reported positions</span>
      <span><i class="m6-trajectory__legend-dot"></i>Largest reported position</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="m6-trajectory__chart">
    <div class="m6-trajectory__axis" aria-hidden="true"><span>100%</span><span>50%</span><span>0%</span></div>
    <ol class="m6-trajectory__quarters" aria-label="Six quarters on a shared zero to one hundred percent scale">
    {% for q in quarters %}
    <li class="m6-trajectory__quarter">
      <strong>{{ q.label }}</strong>
      <div class="m6-trajectory__scale" aria-label="{{ q.label }}: top five {{ '%.1f'|format(q.top5_weight * 100) }}%; largest reported position {{ '%.1f'|format(q.leader_share * 100) }}%">
        <span class="m6-trajectory__bar" style="--m6-top-five: {{ q.top5_weight }}"></span>
        <span class="m6-trajectory__leader" style="--m6-leader: {{ q.leader_share }}"></span>
      </div>
      <span class="m6-trajectory__value">Top five {{ "%.1f"|format(q.top5_weight * 100) }}%</span>
      <span class="m6-trajectory__value">Leader {{ "%.1f"|format(q.leader_share * 100) }}%</span>
      <span class="m6-trajectory__effective">Effective names {{ "%.2f"|format(q.effective_names) }}</span>
      <small>as of {{ q.as_of }}<br>known at {{ q.known_at }}</small>
    </li>
    {% endfor %}
    </ol>
  </div>
  {% if v.timeline.first_majority_crossing %}
  <p class="m6-crossing"><strong>{{ v.timeline.first_majority_crossing.label }}</strong> is the
    first reported quarter in which the largest reported position exceeds 50%
    ({{ "%.1f"|format(v.timeline.first_majority_crossing.share * 100) }}%).
    <small>as of {{ v.timeline.first_majority_crossing.as_of }} &middot;
      known at {{ v.timeline.first_majority_crossing.known_at }} &middot;
      {{ v.timeline.first_majority_crossing.lag_days }}-day lag</small></p>
  {% endif %}
</section>

<section class="m6-gate" aria-labelledby="m6-gate-title">
  <h2 id="m6-gate-title">Can the visible filing support a book-level conclusion?</h2>
  <div class="m6-gate__grid">
    <article class="m6-filer m6-filer--pass" data-filer="vesper">
      <header><h3>{{ v.name }}</h3>
        <span class="verdict-chip" data-verdict="pos">Coverage check passed</span></header>
      <p><strong>{{ "%.1f"|format(v.coverage * 100) }}%</strong> of true gross long weight is
        usable in the public crop (threshold {{ "%.0f"|format(v.gate.threshold * 100) }}%).</p>
      <dl class="m6-stats">
        <div data-stat="concentration"><dt>Latest effective names</dt>
          <dd>{{ "%.2f"|format(v.concentration.effective_names) }}</dd></div>
        <div data-stat="overlap"><dt>Pooled-peer cosine</dt>
          <dd>{{ "%.2f"|format(v.overlap) }}</dd></div>
      </dl>
      <p class="m6-source-dates">as of {{ v.as_of }} &middot; known at {{ v.known_at }} &middot; 45-day lag</p>
      <p>The overlap is descriptive: it says the public books share some names;
        <strong>A separate crowding analysis sets any position cap</strong>.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="m6-filer m6-filer--refuse" data-filer="hensley">
      <header><h3>{{ h.name }}</h3>
        <span class="verdict-chip" data-verdict="neutral">Coverage too low</span></header>
      <p>Only <strong>{{ "%.1f"|format(h.coverage * 100) }}%</strong> of true gross long weight is
        visible, below {{ "%.0f"|format(h.gate.threshold * 100) }}%.
        <strong>Coverage not sufficient to calculate concentration or overlap.</strong></p>
      <div class="power-gate"><span class="power-gate__title">Minimum coverage required</span>
        <p class="power-gate__reason">Visible {{ "%.1f"|format(h.coverage * 100) }}% &lt;
          required {{ "%.0f"|format(h.gate.threshold * 100) }}%: book-level verdicts suppressed.</p>
      </div>
      <p class="m6-source-dates">as of {{ h.as_of }} &middot; known at {{ h.known_at }} &middot; 45-day lag</p>
      <p>Persistence survives only as a hedged fact: these <strong>visible names</strong> have
        persisted in the reported crop; the hidden book may differ.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="m6-holdings-detail" aria-labelledby="m6-holdings-title">
  <h2 id="m6-holdings-title">Reported holdings detail</h2>
  <p>The table supports the trajectory. Labels are presentation names for synthetic securities;
    the public filing arithmetic is unchanged.</p>
  <div class="m6-table-wrap">
    <table class="m6-table">
      <caption>Reported shares and current quarters-held count for {{ v.name }}</caption>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th scope="col">Visible position</th>
          {% for q in quarters %}
          <th scope="col"><span>{{ q.label }}</span>
            <small>as of {{ q.as_of }}<br>known at {{ q.known_at }}<br>45-day lag</small></th>
          {% endfor %}
          <th scope="col">Quarters held</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {% for position in v.timeline.positions %}
        <tr>
          <th scope="row">Position {{ loop.index }}</th>
          {% for share in position.shares %}
          <td style="--m6-share: {{ share }}">{{ "%.1f"|format(share * 100) }}%</td>
          {% endfor %}
          <td><span class="m6-held" style="--m6-held: {{ position.quarters_held }}">
            {{ position.quarters_held }} quarters</span></td>
        </tr>
        {% endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="m6-finra" aria-labelledby="m6-finra-title">
  <h2 id="m6-finra-title">Short-interest stress on top longs</h2>
  <span class="tier-badge">Requires public FINRA data</span>
  <p>No public short-interest series is fabricated. The required series has not been connected,
    so the exhibit leaves days-to-cover blank.</p>
</section>

<section class="m6-caveats" aria-labelledby="m6-caveats-title">
  <h2 id="m6-caveats-title">Four limits to carry into the meeting</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><span class="tier-badge">Staleness</span> {{ card_data.caveats[0] }}</li>
    <li><span class="tier-badge">Longs-only</span> {{ card_data.caveats[1] }}</li>
    <li><span class="tier-badge">Coverage holes</span> {{ card_data.caveats[2] }}</li>
    <li><span class="tier-badge">Option-notional</span> {{ card_data.caveats[3] }} The binding
      current rule is explicit: option lines are excluded and a filer is flagged only above 10%.</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<aside class="m6-boundary" role="note">
  <strong>Method boundary.</strong> Quarters-held is quarterly survival at filing granularity,
  never a half-life and never entry-dated. It is not an alpha-decay curve, allocation rule,
  redemption trigger, or automatic action.
</aside>
{% endblock %}

{% block methodology %}
<p>The emitter takes the existing signed monthly weights at quarter ends, clips shorts to zero,
removes ineligible and option lines, and renormalizes the remaining visible longs. Top-5 share,
Herfindahl, inverse-Herfindahl effective names, quarters-held, and cosine overlap are exact
functions of that crop. No estimator or return model is fitted.</p>
<p>Coverage divides usable visible long weight by the simulator&rsquo;s true positive long weight.
The denominator is known only because this exhibit is synthetic. Live coverage must be inferred
from disclosed gross, withheld-position evidence, and option share; the exact 45-calendar-day
staleness distortion audit remains deferred because the simulator has monthly, not daily, holdings.</p>
{% endblock %}
